  "system": {
    "description": "<p>When rolling for <strong>Dramaturg</strong>, instead of the typical success, your Masks can create their own bodies and give the personalities physical form without being attached to sleepers. In addition, you can give them an appearance matching anyone you’ve met (Arlecchino looks like you, the Innamorati look like two security guards, Capitano looks like the president, etc.) and they will move through the world pretending to be that person. They will do their best, but cannot act outside of their personalities.</p><p>Their Masks will return to you when you dismiss them, the next time you sleep, or when you use Dramaturg again.</p>",
